    <h2>1Ô∏è‚É£ Transformadores Personalizados</h2>

    <h3>Eliminar filas con valores nulos</h3>

    <pre><code>
from sklearn.base import BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin

class DeleteNanRows(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self

    def transform(self, X, y=None):
        return X.dropna()
    </code></pre>

    <h3>Codificaci√≥n One-Hot personalizada</h3>

    <pre><code>
from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder
import pandas as pd

class CustomOneHotEncoder(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    def __init__(self, sparse=False):
        self._oh = OneHotEncoder(
            sparse=sparse,
            handle_unknown='ignore'
        )

    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        x_cat = X.select_dtypes(include=['object'])
        self._oh.fit(x_cat)
        self.feature_names_ = self._oh.get_feature_names_out(x_cat.columns)
        return self

    def transform(self, X, y=None):
        x_cat = X.select_dtypes(include=['object'])
        x_num = X.select_dtypes(exclude=['object'])
        x_cat_oh = self._oh.transform(x_cat)
        x_cat_df = pd.DataFrame(
            x_cat_oh,
            columns=self.feature_names_,
            index=X.index
        )
        return pd.concat([x_num, x_cat_df], axis=1)
    </code></pre>

    <h2>2Ô∏è‚É£ Pipelines Personalizados</h2>

    <p>
        Los Pipelines permiten agrupar m√∫ltiples transformaciones en un solo flujo
        de procesamiento, mejorando la reutilizaci√≥n y organizaci√≥n del c√≥digo.
    </p>

    <h3>Pipeline para atributos num√©ricos</h3>

    <pre><code>
from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline
from sklearn.preprocessing import RobustScaler
from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer

num_pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy="median")),
    ('scaler', RobustScaler())
])
    </code></pre>

    <h2>3Ô∏è‚É£ ColumnTransformer</h2>

    <p>
        <strong>ColumnTransformer</strong> permite ejecutar m√∫ltiples pipelines en paralelo
        y concatenar sus resultados en una sola matriz num√©rica.
    </p>

    <pre><code>
from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer
from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder

num_attributes = list(X_train.select_dtypes(exclude=['object']).columns)
cat_attributes = list(X_train.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns)

full_pipeline = ColumnTransformer([
    ("num", num_pipeline, num_attributes),
    ("cat", OneHotEncoder(
        sparse_output=False,
        handle_unknown='ignore'
    ), cat_attributes)
])

X_train_prep = full_pipeline.fit_transform(X_train)
    </code></pre>

